                <head>No. 368.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1" type="from">Fish</persName> to
                        General <persName corresp="#p_DES1" type="to">Sickles</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-12-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 23, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Urge the immediate release and restoration of embargoed property belonging to
                    American citizens, especially of those whose release has been promised. It is
                    important that there be no further delay. Several estates whose release has been
                    promised have recently been advertised to be leased, and are still held by the
                    authorities in Cuba, in defiance of assurances given in Madrid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HF1">FISH</persName>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
